criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Pediatric surgery patients;

          -  Weight: 2 Kg or more;

          -  Using of a double-lumen short-term central venous catheter (CVC);

          -  CVC realized at operation room, Pediatric Intensive Care Unit (PICU) or Neonatal
             Intensive Care Unit (NICU);

          -  CVC adequately positioned (checked by radioscopy ou radiography);

          -  CVC implanted within a maximum of 24 hours.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients whose implantation of the catheter won't comply with all antisepsis and
             asepsis techniques determined by the study;

          -  History of hypersensitivity, reaction or allergy to ethanol;

          -  Critically ill patients requiring uninterrupted use of both catheter lumens for
             infusion of venous therapy.
